&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;SpyCloud is on a mission to make the internet a safer place by disrupting the criminal underground. SpyCloud’s solutions thwart cyberattacks and protect more than 4 billion accounts worldwide. Cybersecurity is an exciting, evolving space, and being at the forefront of the fight to disrupt cybercrime makes SpyCloud a special place to work. If you’re driven to align your career with a fantastic mission, look no further!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As the Manager, Content Marketing at SpyCloud, you will own the strategy, execution, and performance of content across the buyer journey – from awareness to retention. This role reports to the VP, Brand &amp;amp; Communications and sits at the intersection of storytelling and demand gen, producing content that educates security practitioners, influences buyers, and earns citations from both search engines and AI platforms. You will lead a small but high-output team of content creators working cross-functionally to develop compelling content that resonates with our target audiences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you thrive in a fast-moving B2B environment and know how to turn complex technical topics into engaging content that actually moves pipeline, this role is for you. We invite you to join a winning team that protects digital identities and defends against cyber threats on a global scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content Strategy &amp;amp; Planning: Own the content strategy and monthly roadmap, aligned to product launches, events, and trending topics. Communicate, maintain and enforce an editorial calendar that keeps the team focused and on schedule.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Content Creation &amp;amp; Quality: Lead the production of high-quality and engaging content across a variety of formats, including blog posts, web pages, research reports, case studies, infographics, and videos. Uphold the bar for accuracy, voice, and editorial standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;SEO/AEO Optimization: Partner with our in-house team to optimize content for search visibility and AEO to drive site traffic and qualified conversions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thought Leadership: Collaborate with subject matter experts to develop thought leadership content that earns SpyCloud recognition as the authoritative voice in identity threat protection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Generation: Develop assets that support lead generation and nurture campaigns in collaboration with the demand gen and product marketing teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Distribution &amp;amp; Amplification: Plan and execute multi-channel distribution strategies across web, email, and social channels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Audience &amp;amp; Industry Segmentation: Map content to target personas and key verticals, tailoring messaging to specific pain points and buying triggers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance &amp;amp; Optimization: Analyze content performance metrics and use data to optimize content strategies and prioritize the highest-impact content.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Team Leadership: Lead and mentor a team of content creators and agency partners, fostering a collaborative and high-impact creative culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Brand Voice Governance: Serve as a steward of SpyCloud&#39;s editorial voice and content standards across all channels and contributors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience in cybersecurity content marketing, with strong experience in writing and copy-editing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in Marketing, Communications, Journalism, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track record of building content programs that demonstrably contributed to pipeline and revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong storytelling skills and the ability to t

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;SpyCloud is on a mission to make the internet a safer place by disrupting the criminal underground. SpyCloud’s solutions thwart cyberattacks and protect more than 4 billion accounts worldwide. Cybersecurity is an exciting, evolving space, and being at the forefront of the fight to disrupt cybercrime makes SpyCloud a special place to work. If you’re driven to align your career with a fantastic mission, look no further!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an experienced Manager, Federal Sales Engineering to lead our public sector&amp;nbsp;pre-sales effort in a true player-coach role. You will spend roughly half your time leading and&amp;nbsp;developing a small team of federal sales engineers, and the other half hands-on in strategic&amp;nbsp;engagements: running demos, scoping proofs of concept, and supporting discovery with civilian&amp;nbsp;agencies, the Department of Defense, the intelligence community, and federal law enforcement.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a senior role for a deeply technical cybersecurity leader who understands the federal market and the distinct missions, environments, and buying behavior of the DoD, the Intelligence Community, and federal law enforcement. You will work side by side with federal sales leadership and partners to turn SpyCloud’s breach, malware, and identity data into mission outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is remote, but the person in this position must reside (or relocate to) the Washington D.C. Metro Area to visit Federal clients as needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You&#39;ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Operate as a player-coach. &lt;/strong&gt;Split your time evenly between managing the federal SE team and personally owning pre-sales efforts on strategic agency and partner accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead and mentor&lt;/strong&gt; a team of federal sales engineers, setting the standard for demos, proofs of concept, and technical discovery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner with federal sales leadership&lt;/strong&gt; to ensure coverage across civilian, defense, intelligence, and law enforcement accounts, tailored to each agency&#39;s mission and environment.&lt;/li&gt;
